&lt;h1&gt;Medical Secretary&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a medical secretary to join our team in General Surgery at the Royal United Hospital in Bath working for 30 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide comprehensive secretarial support to two upper GI consultants and their teams within General Surgery and be part of the team providing a general administrative service to the speciality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be an enthusiastic, self-motivated individual who is well organised and has excellent communication skills. You will be flexible and used to working under pressure and to tight deadlines. The successful applicant will be proficient in Microsoft Word, audio typing and diary management. Medical secretarial experience is preferred although training can be given. You will be an effective team player with a flexible approach who can plan and organise their workload, prioritising as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need a good standard of general education – educated to GCSE level or above with relevant secretarial qualifications – RSA III or equivalent. Previous experience in the NHS would be an asset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to be part of this very busy, but friendly department, with high quality staff working together to provide excellent patient care, and wish to discuss the vacancy informally, please contact Gill Maxwell, Team Leader for General Surgery, on 01225 824922 or email g.maxwell@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
